<p>Among aperiodic words, the largest possible palindromic density is achieved by the <a href="/wiki/Fibonacci_word" title="Fibonacci word">Fibonacci word</a>, which has density 1/φ, where φ is the <a href="/wiki/Golden_ratio" title="Golden ratio">Golden ratio</a>.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-AB443&#95;57-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-AB443-57"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>57<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>A <b>palstar</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Concatenation" title="Concatenation">concatenation</a> of palindromic strings, excluding the trivial one-letter palindromes – otherwise all strings would be palstars.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-Jewels&#95;55-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Jewels-55"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>55<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
